If this learned critic knew more of what goes cn in the world, he would not believe that a man of rank could be well flogged by an injured husband without the story being known, even if both the adulterer and the husband and wife said nothing about it. How does he suppose that Sallust could get out of Milo’s house, or out of any house after such treatment without all the slaves knowing it, and others too?
